text:
Court Street, at the S.E. corner of Nelson Street, showing the school of St. Mary's R.C. Church, Star of the Sea.

July 4, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(1)
Gowanus Canal, west side, at Lorraine Street, showing to the right of the Sapolin Co. Building (foreground) the West 9th Street elevated bridge of the Independent Subway Line. In the background (left) is St. Mary, Star of the Sea R.C. Church on Court and Nelson Streets. October 4, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, showing at the right foreground Bowne Stores' warehouse at 611 Smith Street, beyond which on the east bank of Gowanus Canal is a tank of the Brooklyn Union Gas Co. October 4, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, another angle. October 4, 1934.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Gowanus Canal - Brooklyn - Lorraine Street.
